Since the East-West Schism of 1054 the churches that remained in communion with the See of Rome ( the diocese of Rome and its bishop the Pope the primal patriarch ) continued to call itself " Catholic " while the Eastern churches that rejected the Pope 's primal authority have generally been known as " Orthodox " or " Eastern Orthodox " .

Ordained Catholics as well as members of the laity may enter into consecrated life either on an individual basis as a hermit or consecrated virgin or by joining an institute of consecrated life ( a religious institute or a secular institute ) in which to take vows confirming their desire to follow the three evangelical counsels of chastity poverty and obedience .

CCC 12001209 In the definition of the Code of Canons of the Eastern Churches " a rite is the liturgical theological spiritual and disciplinary patrimony culture and circumstances of history of a distinct people by which its own manner of living the faith is manifested in each Church sui iuris " The is " Ritus est patrimonium liturgicum theologicum spirituale et disciplinare cultura ac rerum adiunctis historiae populorum distinctum quod modo fidei vivendae uniuscuiusque Ecclesiae sui iuris proprio exprimitur .

was lodged

alleging that the Pope of the Congregation of the Doctrine of the Faith had committed a crime against humanity by failing to prevent perpetrators of rape in a systematic concealment 848 15 July 2010 2010-10-28 In September 2011

15 July 2010 2010-10-28 In September 2011 a submission was lodged with the International Criminal Court alleging that the Pope Cardinal Angelo Sodano dean of the College of Cardinals Cardinal Tarcisio Bertone Vatican Secretary of State and Cardinal William Levada head of the Congregation of the Doctrine of the Faith had committed a crime against humanity by failing to prevent or punish perpetrators of rape and sexual violence in a " systematic and widespread " concealment which included failure to co-operate with relevant law enforcement agencies .

William_Levada

the Cardinal William Levada head of the Congregation of the Doctrine of the Faith

had committed

a crime against humanity by failing to punish perpetrators of rape in a systematic concealment

15 July 2010 2010-10-28 In September 2011 a submission was lodged with the International Criminal Court alleging that the Pope Cardinal Angelo Sodano dean of the College of Cardinals Cardinal Tarcisio Bertone Vatican Secretary of State and Cardinal William Levada head of the Congregation of the Doctrine of the Faith had committed a crime against humanity by failing to prevent or punish perpetrators of rape and sexual violence in a " systematic and widespread " concealment which included failure to co-operate with relevant law enforcement agencies .
